<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-065-444  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 065 444.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Feb 13 1990 v9 n3 p387(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hostage: you save a US embassy from terrorists. (Software Review)(Mindscape Hostage computer game)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Trivette, Don.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mindscape Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    MIND.andO;Product:   Hostage (Computer game).andO;Topic:     Computer gamesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Hostage: You Save A U.S.andP;  Embassy from Terrorists Highly trained marksmentook up positions outside the embassy today, as an assault team rappeled downfrom the roof and crashed through the window.andP;  Once inside, the team of threecommandos located the hostages and led them to a safe room on the thirdfloor.andP;  Casualty reports are incomplete, but a number of terrorists areconfirmed dead.andM;The six o'clock news?andP;  No.andP;  This is Hostage, an action game from Mindscape.andO;As the lieutenant in charge of the operation, your job is to rescue hostagesfrom an overrun embassy.andP;  At your command are six men with code names Delta,Echo, Mike, Hotel, Tango, and Bravo.andP;  You control each of the sixindividually and can switch from one to another simply by pressing acorresponding function key.andM;The rescue is made in four stages: surrounding the building, rapelling fromthe roof, finding the hostages and subduing the terrorists, and reviewing theresults.andP;  If there's anything wrong with Hostage, it is that the briefingbooklet gives away too much.andP;  It tells you where to station yoursharpshooters and how to secure the hostages.andP;  But the doing is moredifficult than the telling.andP;  There are lots of little things the book doesn'ttell you.andM;Once you are inside the building, a small diagram on the screen shows wherehostages, terrorists, and your own men are positioned; the greater part ofthe screen presents a three-dimensional view through the eyes of the man youare controlling.andP;  You work your way from room to room, blasting terroristsand collecting hostages one at a time.andP;  But even after the hostages aresecured in the windowless room on the third-floor, you've got to keep an eyeout lest a stray terrorist sneak in and waste everybody.andM;There are five levels of play, ranging from Training to Assault; each ofthese may be played as Lieutenant, Captain, or Commander, giving you a totalof 15 different scenarios.andP;  You begin at the lowest rank and work your way upby successfully completing the mission, at which time you are awarded apromotion and a password that lets you play future games at a higher rank.andO;I'm still playing as a Lieutenant although several of my friends have madeCaptain.andM;Hostage appears to be a harmless little game, but gamers beware: somehow youjust can't put it down until everyone is safe.andO;</TEXT></DOC>